throughout 2022, my favorite Seattle radio station KEXP celebrated their 50th anniversary each week by selecting a week at random between 1972 and 2022 and playing music from that year the points along the yellow curve represent how many years have passed since the years they selected.
i added over 1,000 songs to my shazams playlist on spotify in 2022 many of these songs were played on KEXP the blue curve represents how many tracks were added to the playlist each week

i used the spotify API and the spotifyr R package to retrieve the metadata for every track on my shazams playlist the green curve represents the average age of tracks added to the playlist each week note that spotify does not always include the original release date of tracks if they were remastered later
the 22 orange points represent some of my favorite tracks added to my shazams playlist in 2022 the distance from the timeline represents the age of these tracks
<text>
of all the weeks in 2022, I added the most tracks to my shazams playlist during the the week of nov 18  KEXP was profiling 1978 and 1990 that week
i was sick with covid at the end of September, listening to a lot of KEXP as i recovered, enjoying the music of 1995 and 1976

"can you feel what i'm saying" is the oldest track among my favorites i heard it in the car on the way to a prenatal appointment my son was born the next day and in the weeks that followed we listened to a lot of minnie riperton
this nujabes track is the newest among my favorites (2003), however, it samples an 1989 track called "clouds" by gigi masin
according to my spotify year wrapped for 2022, the artist i listened to the most was david sylvian, band leader of japan and later rain tree crow (1990)
"the downtown lights" is easily my favorite track of any of those i heard for the first time in 2022 i heard it as part of totally enormous extinct dinosaurs' dj set for the lot radio in april
i hadn't heard "dangerous" in about 30 years!
i was traveling in hawaii in april, not listening to as much music
i clearly love the music of 1991 in the month of June
listen to my favorites from 2022 here: https://open.spotify.com/playlist/40GbJmwV9ldT3OftTgH5aF?si=fe36b0e64ab84e6a
looks like i was focused with work in February, ignoring music or forgetting to add tracks to my shazams playlist
traveled to a family wedding in early september not much time for private music listening
